directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cut each biscuit into fourths and place in a large bowl. Add in onion and garlic powder, parsley, cheese and olive oil. Mix well.
Place 3-4 pieces into each muffin cup ( prepared with non stick spray.) I got 9 biscuits out of my tube. Bake at 375 degrees for 10-13 minutes, until biscuits are golden.
title: Easy Cheesy Pull Apart Rolls
